Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a full #kettle. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press).

In a large #bowl, break up the @unconventional plant-based burgers{2} into a large bowl and combine with the garlic, @breadcrumbs{10%g}, @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Using your hands, mix together well and shape into balls, 2 per person.

Place the plant-based meatballs onto a lined #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your #oven until browned on the outside, ~{12-14%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1}, then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

== Couscous ==

Put the @couscous{120%g} in a #bowl. Pour in the @boiled water{200%ml}, stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, then cover tightly with #cling film{}.

Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the grated carrot, remaining roasted spice and herb blend (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and remaining garlic. Fry until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, vegetable stock paste, @sugar{3/4%tsp} and @water{100%ml}. Cook until thickened, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the plant-based meatballs are cooked, gently stir them through the sauce. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

== To Serve ==

When ready, fluff up the couscous with a #fork and share between your bowls.

Top with the Lebanese style plant-based meatballs, spooning over the tomato sauce from the pan.

Scatter over the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g} to finish.

Enjoy!